transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks, Paul Viagra, Quinn speaking. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, sir. I want to cancel my subscriptions.

Speaker 1: Okay, one moment. Is your name Peter?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: No, I just decided not to spend the money.

Speaker 2: Okay, well you do not have to get this so frequently or monthly.

Speaker 1: You can choose when you get your next order. That's easier for you. You can call in for your next one.

Speaker 2: Why don't I call for my next one then?

Speaker 1: Yeah, that's how I can set it up for you now.

Speaker 2: Okay, so basically we just keep your prescription available to you for the next five months,

Speaker 1: and you don't have to call us for your next order, okay?

Speaker 2: Yep, that's just a number. Is that your number?

Speaker 1: Correct, yeah, and I can also give you my extension as well.

Speaker 2: So I can put your orders in and make sure your account stays like this for you.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: And my extension is 0035.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: All right, well you are all set, sir. I did make those changes for you.

Speaker 1: All right, thank you.
